    "enterprise_promise": "SecurityRecipes can prove that human input requests from MCP servers are identity-bound, mode-aware, consented, URL-safe, and logged before user data or third-party authorization enters the agentic workflow.",
    "why_now": "MCP 2025-11-25 introduced URL-mode elicitation for sensitive flows that must not pass through the MCP client. That is an enterprise-grade feature, but it creates a new trust boundary: users can be phished, forms can request secrets, URLs can carry sensitive data, and servers can confuse external authorization with MCP authorization unless clients enforce a structured policy."
